 0      7 0             16 0             16
+--------+----------------+----------------+
|   TTY  |  COLUMN COUNT  |    ROW COUNT   |
+--------+----------------+----------------+

TTY          is a boolean field denoting whether or not a TTY is wanted.
COLUMN COUNT is a 16bit integer denoting the TTY's column count.
ROW COUNT    is a 16bit integer denoting the TTY's row count.

If TTY is false then latter fields might be filled with arbitrary values
that will be ignored by the server.